      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>couscous</strong> to a heatproof bowl with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> boiled water, cover and set aside until all of the liquid has been absorbed</p><p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine the <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> with 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>honey-Dijon dressing</strong></p>",
